aused by natal kicks removing the r-process sources far from their birth\nsites, making enrichment more inhomogeneous, rather than the usual\ninterpretation that the scatter is set by the rarity of its production source.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Oct 2021 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 11 Mar 2022 16:57:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-30"}
